<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,979,1357]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="C.Presl, 1851" authorityName="C.Presl" authorityYear="1851" box="[312,436,979,1005]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Mecodium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,436,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mecodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
potentially groups five species in the area including eastern and southern Africa and the western Indian Ocean. These species are morphologically close and are thus often confused (
<figureCitation box="[198,270,1049,1076]" captionStart="Fig. 5" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1783,1809]" captionTargetBox="[196,1392,265,1747]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1392,265,1747]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 5. Western Indian Ocean Hymenophyllum subg. Mecodium, illustrating morphological resemblance of taxa which are difficult to distinguish (see text). A. Hymenophyllum kuhnii C. Chr. from Comoros, firstly identified as H. polyanthos (Sw.) Sw. (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6864, P 00312328). B. Hymenophyllum capense Schrad. from Madagascar, initially identified as H. fumarioides Bory ex Willd. (F. Rakotondrainibe et al. 6121, P 00212664). C. Syntype of Hymenophyllum kuhnii C. Chr. from Tanzania (B 200092782). D. Hymenophyllum inaequale (Poir.) Desv., representative specimen from La Réunion (L. Bauret 190, P)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/896413/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): paleotropical populations of supposedly 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sw.) Sw." authorityName="(Sw.) Sw." box="[771,1059,1049,1075]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polyanthos">
<emphasis box="[771,936,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. polyanthos</emphasis>
(Sw.) Sw.
</taxonomicName>
, East and South-African and Indian Ocean 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrad." authorityName="Schrad., Gottingische" authorityYear="1818" box="[356,587,1084,1110]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[356,486,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. capense</emphasis>
Schrad.
</taxonomicName>
, East and South-African 
<taxonomicName authority="C. Chr." authorityName="C.Chr." box="[886,1083,1084,1110]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kuhnii">
<emphasis box="[886,995,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. kuhnii</emphasis>
C.Chr.
</taxonomicName>
, the western Indian Ocean 
<taxonomicName authority="Bory ex Willd." authorityName="Bory ex Willd." box="[189,558,1119,1146]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fumarioides">
<emphasis box="[189,368,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. fumarioides</emphasis>
Bory ex Willd.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Poir.) Desv. In" authorityName="(Poir.) Desv. In" box="[620,969,1119,1146]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequale">
<emphasis box="[620,775,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. inaequale</emphasis>
(Poir.) Desv. In
</taxonomicName>
the fern flora of South Africa, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sim T. R." journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Sim T. R. 1915. The ferns of South Africa. The University Press, Cambridge." title="The ferns of South Africa" type="book" year="1915">Sim (1915)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrad., Gottingische" authorityYear="1818" box="[408,538,1155,1180]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[408,538,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[743,919,1155,1181]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fumarioides">
<emphasis box="[743,919,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. fumarioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[983,1135,1155,1181]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequale">
<emphasis box="[983,1135,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. inaequale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is cited in the area but not 
<taxonomicName box="[233,342,1190,1216]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kuhnii">
<emphasis box="[233,342,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. kuhnii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contrary to the other more recent local floras (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Burrows J. E." box="[943,1114,1190,1216]" journalOrPublisher="Frandsen Publisher, Sandton" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Burrows J. E. 1990. Southern African ferns and fern allies. Frandsen Publisher, Sandton." title="Southern African ferns and fern allies" type="book" year="1990">Burrows 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[1133,1282,1190,1216]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux (2009)</bibRefCitation>
restricted 
<taxonomicName box="[189,369,1225,1251]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fumarioides">
<emphasis box="[189,369,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. fumarioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the type is a mixed collect from Mauritius and La Réunion: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">J.B.G.M. Bory de St.­ Vincent 119</emphasis>
, holotype BW20229010, isotype P00547028) and 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1097,1260,1286]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequale">
<emphasis box="[942,1097,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. inaequale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Indian Ocean and Tanzania, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrad., Gottingische" authorityYear="1818" box="[311,442,1296,1321]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[311,442,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being treated as a distinct species with a wider distribution including the Indian Ocean, eastern Africa and South-Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1396,1458]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Our investigations allowed us to recognize and propose here only three species for subg. 
<taxonomicName authority="C.Presl, 1851" authorityName="C.Presl" authorityYear="1851" box="[1244,1368,1396,1422]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Mecodium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1244,1368,1396,1422]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mecodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the archipelago as we will discuss here-after. These species are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schrad., Gottingische" authorityYear="1818" box="[930,1060,1432,1457]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capense">
<emphasis box="[930,1060,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. capense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1226,1431,1457]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequale">
<emphasis box="[1075,1226,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. inaequale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1282,1391,1431,1457]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Hymenophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kuhnii">
<emphasis box="[1282,1391,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. kuhnii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
